
### Pushgateway with nginx to setup basic authentication

```bash
# Install apache2-utils if you don't have it (example for Debian/Ubuntu)
# sudo apt install apache2-utils

# Create a directory for Nginx config and the password file
mkdir -p nginx_conf

# Generate the password file. The command will prompt you for a password.
# Replace 'pushgateway_user' with your desired username.
htpasswd -c nginx_conf/.htpasswd pushgateway_user
```